Subject: =?UTF-8?q?feat(slayzone):=20extension=20bar=20=E2=80=94=20see=20+?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20open=20each=20extension=20in=20the=20modal?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The chromeless inlay removed Chrome's extension toolbar, leaving installed
extensions (1Password) with no entry point. Add a minimal one: a rail in the
extensions modal that lists the identity's extensions and opens each one's UI.

- mojom: ListExtensions(profile_key) => array<ExtensionInfo{id, name, enabled,
  has_options, has_popup}>; OpenExtensionOptions(id); OpenExtensionPopup(id).
- Host: enumerate ExtensionRegistry::Get(profile)->enabled_extensions() (skip
  component + non-extension); has_options via OptionsPageInfo, has_popup via
  ExtensionActionManager/ExtensionAction. OpenExtensionOptions →
  ExtensionTabUtil::OpenOptionsPage; OpenExtensionPopup → navigate the inlay's
  active tab to the action's popup URL (the extension's own UI, e.g. the
  1Password vault).
- slayzone_shell_ui: widen the img-src CSP with chrome://extension-icon so the
  rail renders real extension icons.

Per-identity (Work's extensions vs Personal's). Verified: 1Password's icon + its
popup UI load in the modal body.
